    ,Place(name: 'Zorbas, Zakynthou',url: 'https://www.zorbas.com.cy/', imagePath: 'larnacaRest/zorpas1.jpg', lat: 34.92618817533569,long: 33.633464968220345, id: 172, category: 'Bakery/Food', city: 'Larnaca', description: 'Zorbas Bakeries is a renowned bakery chain in Cyprus, known for its rich history and wide array of offerings. The company started about 50 years ago as a small family bakery and has since expanded to multiple locations across Cyprus. They focus on providing quality choices with high nutritional value and superior taste, emphasizing craftsmanship and tradition in their baking methods.Zorbas offers a variety of products, including bakery items, confectioneries, a selection of foods, and juices. They are particularly famous for their slow-fermented bread, known for its rich texture and thin, crispy crust. Their menu also includes warm dishes like rotisserie chicken, peas in tomato sauce, salads, sandwiches, and yoghurt meals.' )
    ,Place(name: 'To Mpalkonaki',id: 8016, imagePath: 'larnacaRest/det_to_mpalkonaki.jpg',lat: 34.915089305814725, long: 33.63723830264436, category: 'Restaurant, Traditional Food', city: 'Larnaca', url: 'https://facebook.com/TOMPALKONAKI2020/', description: '"To Mpalkonaki" in Larnaca is a quaint and charming café that captures the essence of Cypriot hospitality. Its name, translating to "The Little Balcony" in English, hints at its cozy and intimate setting, often adorned with flowering plants and offering a picturesque view of the bustling streets of Larnaca. This café is a favorite among locals and tourists alike for its warm atmosphere and authentic Cypriot cuisine (photo form Wizz-Guide).')
