   ,Place(name: 'Alexander',url: 'https://www.tripadvisor.com.gr/Restaurant_Review-g190379-d2664098-Reviews-Alexander-Larnaca_Larnaka_District.html', imagePath: 'larnacaRest/alexander.jpg', lat: 34.91203239849234, long: 33.63772645905195,city: 'Larnaca',id: 1042, category: 'Restaurant, Traditional Food', description: 'Alexander Restaurant in Larnaca, located on the scenic Finikoudes beach, is a culinary gem that caters to lovers of traditional Cypriot cuisine. This restaurant boasts a diverse menu that includes an array of salads, appetizers, soups, and a variety of meat and fish dishes. Their seafood offerings are particularly notable, alongside homemade pirogis, pizza, and delectable desserts. Patrons can complement their meals with a selection of wine and other beverages, making Alexander Restaurant a perfect spot for a delightful dining experience by the sea (photo from Tripadvisor).',)
  , Place(name: 'Edem\'s Yard', imagePath: 'larnacaRest/edms.jpg',url: 'https://www.facebook.com/p/Edems-Yard-100064318377038/', id: 1043, lat: 34.91404868999416, long: 33.636750948785966, category: 'Brunch', city: 'Larnaca', description: 'Edem\'s Yard in Larnaca is a bright and modern spot that has quickly become a favorite among locals and tourists for its delicious food and exceptional service. The restaurant is celebrated for accommodating any meal request from breakfast, brunch to lunch, presenting a new fasting menu that features a variety of vegan options, including hummus avocado toast, Mediterranean pizza bagel, fluffy vegan pancakes, and their special smoked Tokyo, which comes with smoked bacon or smoked salmon (photo from wiz cyprus guide). '),
    Place(name: 'To Arxontikon',lat: 34.913839305867384,long: 33.637750823350025, imagePath: 'larnacaRest/arxontikon.jpg',id: 1044, url: 'https://www.facebook.com/ToArchontikon/', city: 'Larnaca', category: 'Restaurant, Traditional Food', description: 'Arxontikon in Larnaca offers a unique culinary journey set in a mansion built in 1850, recognized for its architectural style and historic value as an ancient monument. The restaurant serves a variety of Cypriot and Greek dishes, emphasizing the tradition of \'meze\', a term that originates from the Persian word \'ma-ze\', meaning \'taste\'. Their commitment to Cypriot hospitality is reflected in their offering of the most delicious meat, fish, and seafood dishes, promising an unparalleled gastronomic experience. The Ultimate Meze at Arxontikon is a feast of over 25 dishes, including fresh fish, seafood, meat, accompanied by dips, salads, and side dishes, alongside a selection of exquisite local and international wines from their cava. The ingredients are highlighted for their freshness and quality, from the tenderest meats and garden-fresh vegetables to the warm baked bread, ensuring every bite is a testament to the finest culinary standards. (photo from Tripadvisor).')
    , Place(name: 'To Edesma tou Paradisou', lat:34.91673107064512, long: 33.63482610008688,imagePath: 'larnacaRest/edesma.jpg',id: 1045, url: 'https://www.facebook.com/ToEdesmaTouParadeisou/',city: 'Larnaca', category: 'Restaurant, Traditional Food', description: 'Edesma tou Paradisou in Larnaca is a traditional tavern that truly embodies the essence of Cypriot and Greek hospitality. The tavern is renowned for its welcoming atmosphere where guests are often greeted with local homemade Zivania or Baklava, showcasing the establishment\'s commitment to authentic local flavors and warm hospitality. Their menu is a celebration of traditional Cypriot cuisine, featuring local fresh meat, potatoes, and vegetables. Specialties include sieftalies and dishes prepared on charcoals, with Souvla of Pork Chicken and Lamb being a highlight during live music nights every Friday and Saturday (photo from Wiz-Guide).'),
    Place(name: 'Ithaki Gardern',lat: 34.914550593719326,long: 33.636010063556455, imagePath: 'larnacaRest/kipos.jpg',id: 1046, url: 'https://www.facebook.com/IthakiGardenResto/', category: 'Restaurant, Mediterranean Food', city: 'Larnaca', description: 'Ithaki Garden in Larnaca is a charming spot that seems to have captured the hearts of many. Nestled amidst a bustling area, this little gem offers a tranquil and peaceful garden setting, making it a perfect escape in the heart of the city. Guests have praised the welcoming vibe, the vibrant flowers, and the greenery that envelops the space, providing a serene atmosphere.The restaurant has garnered positive reviews for its delicious Mediterranean, Barbecue, and Greek cuisine, with options for vegetarian, vegan, and gluten-free diets. Visitors have highlighted dishes such as the grilled stuffed calamari with cheese and peppers, chicken with roasted potatoes, and beef in a juicy tomato sauce, praising the freshness and quality of the ingredients. The crispy feta cheese with honey and sesame seeds as a starter comes highly recommended by patrons (photo form Check In Cyprus).')
